D=10633.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: laaagggg</span><hr size=1> Generally low frame rates are caused by either lack of memory, lack of CPU power or lack of video card power.<br>
<br>
How to figure out where the lag is:<br>
<br>
i) Watch your hard drive light when things get laggy.  If it flickers a lot when lag happens then you need more memory.  EQ's memory usage is around 400M (according to task manager on my XP box) so any less than this has the potential of causing lag.<br>
<br>
ii) Turn your screen resolution down to 640x480.  If the lag goes away then you should upgrade your video card.<br>
<br>
iii) If the lag persists at 640x480 then your CPU is probably overloaded.  Think about upgrading it.<br>
<br>
EQ isn't as hard on the video card as you would initially think.  A fast CPU will go a lot further with EQ than a fast video card (or at least until they get Umbra working properly that's the case).  My Duron 650/GF2MX/768M is definitely CPU bound and not video bound at 1024x768.<br>
<br>
Naturally I turn off spell effects on raids but have never needed my clipping plane changed in any zone other than Shar Vahl.  I run with all the new models off.<br>
<br>
My computer prefers Pavlova to pudding.  It must be because I bought it in Australia.<br>
<br>
