<br>
Exactly, the system to check for if a polygon should be displayed is pretty optimized these days, and it will burn through the polygon list quickly leaving the 1-10 or what have you polygons you need to render the floor.<br>
<br>
This is also why you'll see some people having video lag problems sitting in the corner staring at a wall during raids. Sit against a wall without a lot of features on it facing the closest zone boundary during raids if you can, should help.<br>
<br>
I've got two machines running eq right now.<br>
GeForce2, 512 ram, dual P3 450 - cpu speed is the bounding factor on this one, unfotunately it's hard to find chips slow enough in pairs that the motherboard can handle to upgrade.<br>
<br>
Geforce3, 256 ram, P4 1400 - ram is the bounding factor with luclin models. With luclin models off the only time I've been able to get it to lag was with 4 people casting aes against 30+ mushrooms with particle effects set to high. <p><TABLE BORDER="0">
